com.ibm.team.process.common

Interface IDevelopmentLineState


  • public interface IDevelopmentLineState
    Represents the initial state of a development line as defined by a process definition. When a project area is initialized from a process definition, the process framework instantiates development lines and iterations which correspond to the state specified in the definition.
    Since:
    0.5

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      java.lang.String getDevelopmentLineName()
      Returns the name of the development line to which this process state applies or null if the line is not configured.

      Returns the string describing the end date of the development line.
      java.lang.String getId()

      Returns the collection of iteration states which this development line contains, if any.

      Returns whether this development line is flagged as the project development line.

    • Method Detail

      • getId

        java.lang.String getId()
        Returns the identifier of the development line to which this process state applies or null if the line is not configured.

        In order for this configuration to be saved to the repository this field must have a non-null value, so it is safe to assume that this method will not return null if it comes from a model built from an immutable item fetched from the repository. It is possible for an incomplete/invalid configuration, however, to return null.

        Returns:
        the identifier of the development line to which this process state applies or null

      • getLabel

        java.lang.String getLabel()
        This convenience method returns the name of this line if the name is not null and is not a whitespace string. Otherwise it returns this line's id, which may be null.
        Returns:
